## v3.2 - Verify that sessions are invalidated when the user logs out.

### Why is this required?

Session hacking is a common means for a malicious user to attack a site.  Many session hacking attacks occur because sessions are not properly invalidated.

### Applicability (Level 1)

This objective applies to all apps that contain user sessions.

### Guidelines for developers

Ensure that sessions are deleted when a user either logs out or exits the site.
